Development Plan: Phase Vocoder Time-Stretching
The core algorithmic change
Time-stretching requires decoupling the analysis hop from the synthesis hop:

Analysis hop = how many samples we consume from the input buffer per frame → controls how fast we read the sample
Synthesis hop = how many samples we output per frame → stays fixed at AUDIO_BLOCK_SAMPLES (128) to satisfy Teensy's block rate

stretch_factor = synthesis_hop / analysis_hop

stretch > 1  →  analysis_hop < 128  →  reads input slowly  →  output is longer (slower)
stretch < 1  →  analysis_hop > 128  →  reads input fast    →  output is shorter (faster)
The phase accumulation must use synthesis_hop (what drives the output), while the phase analysis uses analysis_hop (what determines the true instantaneous frequency). Currently the code conflates these — both use STEP_SIZE.

